                Senate
              </span> <span style="text-transform: uppercase">May 13, 2026</span><br/></td></tr></tbody><tbody><tr><td align="center"/></tr></tbody></table></div><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><font size="3" style="FONT-FAMILY: MinionPC, Arial Unicode MS">
                    CALIFORNIA LEGISLATURE—
                    2025–2026 REGULAR SESSION</font></div><br clear="all"/><span id="bill_house_num"><div style="float: left; width:50%; font-weight: bold; "><span style="text-transform: uppercase; text-align:left;width:50%;"><b>
                Assembly Concurrent Resolution
              </b></span></div><div style="float:right; width:50%; text-align:right;"><span style="text-transform: uppercase;"><b>No. 126</b></span></div></span><hr/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><table style="border-collapse: collapse" cellSpacing="0" align="center" role="presentation"><tbody><tr><td id="bill_authors" align="center"><span style="font-weight:bold;">Introduced by Assembly Member Tangipa<br/>(Coauthor: Senator Alvarado-Gil)<br/></span></td></tr><tr><td id="bill_intro_date" align="center" class="textcenter"><br/>January 22, 2026</td></tr></tbody></table></div><hr/><br clear="all"/><div id="title"><span style="font-weight:normal;font-size:0.9em;">Relative to the Captain Vidar Anderson Memorial Highway. </span></div><br clear="all"/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><h2>LEGISLATIVE COUNSEL'S DIGEST</h2></div><br/><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0"><span id="subject">ACR 126, as amended, Tangipa.
                          Captain Vidar Anderson Memorial Highway.</span></div><div><span id="digesttext"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">This measure would designate a specified portion of State Highway Route 395 in the County of Mono as the Captain Vidar Anderson Memorial Highway. The measure would request that the Department of Transportation determine the cost of appropriate signs showing this special designation and, upon receiving donations from nonstate sources sufficient to cover the cost, to erect those signs.</div></span></div><span class="hidden"><h2>Digest Key</h2></span><span id="fiscalcommittee">
      Fiscal Committee:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">YES</span>  </span></div><hr/><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Text</h2></span><span class="Resolution" title="source: /caml:MeasureDoc/caml:Resolution&#xA;    "><span class="Whereas" id="id_68CB8CBD-65B6-42BB-9309-895BE2EE197D"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, On February 19, 1990, at approximately 10:40 a.m., Long Valley Fire Protection District Captain Vidar Anderson, along with 50 other first responders, responded to an emergency call regarding teenagers who had fallen through the ice at Convict Lake; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_7DD26882-18B4-49EC-A2BD-5539E53BE4EE"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Captain Anderson was one of four local responders who fell through the ice in an attempt to rescue the teenagers; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_DB7A642F-C044-42D6-8B52-164AC2235733"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, In his heroic effort to save the teenagers, Captain Anderson also saved the life of his fellow first responder, Long Valley Fire Protection District Chief Chris Baitx; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_E4165ECA-5442-4502-B115-2A1FD65DF5A3"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Tragically, Captain Anderson succumbed to the cold, giving his life in the line of duty while attempting to save others during this tragic event; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_E7C6BC0C-79AE-4E09-B68B-5FA745BAF113"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Captain Anderson’s invaluable service, dedication, leadership, and commitment contributed greatly to the safety and well-being of his community; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_A36A165D-AF50-4A10-8B3B-87B97E7BE0BA"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The Long Valley Fire Protection District seeks to honor Captain Anderson’s memory and service by dedicating a portion of State Route 395 in his name; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_A42A7CA2-FEBA-46F8-93C0-BB55D8B6F83D"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, This dedication will serve as a fitting tribute to Captain Vidar Anderson’s service, sacrifice, and heroism, and will ensure that he is remembered by all who travel this route; now, therefore, be it</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_B807D36F-8A3D-44F1-AC2F-3104E08CD015"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved by the Assembly of the State of California, the Senate thereof concurring, That the Legislature hereby designates the portion of State Route 395, from Rock Creek Road, at postmile R10.264, to the South Landing Overcrossing #47-48, at postmile<font color="#B30000"><strike> R14.080,</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> R13.931,</i></font> in the County of Mono as the Captain Vidar Anderson Memorial Highway; and be it further</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_E80BC9A5-163A-4D79-898F-5265881011E7"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved, That the Department of Transportation is requested to determine the cost of appropriate signs, consistent with the signing requirements for the state highway system, showing this special designation and, upon receiving donations from nonstate sources sufficient to cover the cost, to erect those signs; and be it further</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_D8370D26-4A8B-4050-8980-A9A5BD0AFF24"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved, That the Chief Clerk of the Assembly transmit copies of this resolution to the Director of Transportation and to the author for appropriate distribution.</div></span></span></div></body></html>
